                                         CAPE TOWN - Police in Cape Town have arrested several suspects in connection with various drug-related crimes this week.  Two males and one female suspect were arrested for possession of tik.  A 40-year-old man was also among those arrested after he was caught amid a drug transaction by police The city's Wayne Dyason said, “Officers witnessed a 40-year-old man in a drug transaction, they arrested him for resisting arrest and intimidation.” 